    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2023 R1 is deployed under a validated-software QMS conforming to ISO 9001:2015 and FDA 21 CFR Part 820. Installation qualification (IQ), operational qualification (OQ), and performance qualification (PQ) records are archived. Version control is enforced via Git with signed tags; all simulation scripts are stored in a controlled repository with mandatory peer-review before merge. Regression test suite of 142 benchmark cases is executed on every release branch; pass rate 100% for structural-mechanics suite relevant to this COU.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-sqa",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Software used for regulatory submission must operate under a documented QMS with IQ/OQ/PQ records, version-controlled scripts, and a regression suite demonstrating ≥99% pass rate on relevant benchmark cases. Achieved: all conditions satisfied."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical has been verified against ASME V&V 10 benchmark problems for linear-elastic and elastic-plastic structural analysis. Internal code verification reports (CVR-2022-001 through CVR-2022-014) demonstrate agreement with analytical solutions to within 0.1% for all applicable element types (SOLID186, CONTA174, TARGE170). Patch-test and Taylor-series convergence checks are documented for the element formulations used in this model.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Code must be verified against recognised benchmark problems with documented agreement within 0.5% of analytical solutions for all element types used. Achieved: 0.1% agreement across 14 benchmark cases."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh-convergence study was conducted using five mesh densities (global element size 2.0, 1.5, 1.0, 0.75, 0.5 mm) with Richardson extrapolation applied to construct stiffness and peak von Mises stress at the screw-rod junction. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for the production mesh (1.0 mm global, 0.3 mm at contact interfaces) is GCI=0.31% for stiffness and GCI=0.87% for peak stress, both well below the 2% threshold. p-order of convergence confirmed at 1.97 (theoretical 2.0 for quadratic elements). Discretization error is therefore characterised to better than Gradation 5 requirements.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-disc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — Gradation 4 required, 5 achieved",
        "description": "GCI for all primary QoIs must be <2% on the production mesh. Richardson extrapolation must confirm monotonic convergence. Achieved: GCI=0.31% (stiffness), GCI=0.87% (peak stress); convergence order p=1.97."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solution uses a full Newton-Raphson scheme with line-search. Force residual convergence criterion set to 1×10⁻⁴ (relative) and displacement residual to 1×10⁻⁴; both tighter than solver default. All 11 virtual specimens converged without bisection beyond the first load step. Sparse direct solver (SPARSE) used; iterative solver was tested as a check and produced stiffness values within 0.05% of direct-solver results. Solver log files are archived in the simulation data package.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-solver",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Residual convergence criteria must be ≤1×10⁻³ (relative); solver type must be documented; cross-check with alternative solver required for at least one specimen. Achieved: residuals ≤1×10⁻⁴; direct vs iterative cross-check within 0.05%."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Model setup was performed by a licensed engineer with 8 years FEA experience in orthopaedic device simulation. An independent reviewer with equivalent credentials performed a line-by-line review of all boundary condition definitions, material assignments, contact pair definitions, and load application scripts against the pre-approved simulation protocol (SP-2024-007). Two discrepancies found and corrected before any results were extracted. Formal sign-off documented in review record RR-2024-007-v2.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-use-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Independent technical review of model setup by a qualified engineer against a pre-approved simulation protocol is required. All discrepancies must be resolved and documented before results extraction. Achieved: two-person review completed; discrepancies resolved; formal sign-off recorded."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The FEA model uses a bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) constitutive law for Ti-6Al-4V (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.5 GPa) and a linear-elastic model for the Sawbones surrogate (E=3.0 GPa, ν=0.3). Contact between screw head and polyaxial housing is modelled as frictional (μ=0.25, augmented Lagrangian). Model form was selected based on published literature (Nagaraja 2018, Galbusera 2020) and validated against the experimental dataset. Sensitivity of QoIs to constitutive model choice (BISO vs multilinear isotropic) was quantified; difference <1.5% in all QoIs, confirming BISO is adequate.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Constitutive model selection must be justified by literature and sensitivity analysis. Alternative model forms must be evaluated; difference in primary QoIs must be <5%. Achieved: BISO vs multilinear difference <1.5%; literature justification documented."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Material properties for Ti-6Al-4V were measured on five tensile coupons machined from the same rod stock used in bench testing (mean E=114.2 GPa, CV=0.8%; mean σ_y=882 MPa, CV=1.1%). Sawbones block modulus was characterised by three-point bending of companion specimens (mean E=2.98 GPa, CV=2.3%). Geometric inputs were extracted from CMM measurements of three production screws (OD tolerance ±0.03 mm). All input distributions are documented in material characterisation report MCR-2024-003.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Primary material properties must be measured from test-article-representative specimens with CV documented. Geometric inputs must be derived from dimensional inspection. Achieved: coupon testing (n≥3) and CMM measurements completed; all CVs <5%."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled and tested: six at Laboratory 1 (ISO 17025 accredited) and five at Laboratory 2 (ISO 17025 accredited). All screws were drawn from a single production lot (Lot 2023-NC75-001) with certificate of conformance. Construct assembly was performed by a trained surgical technician following the manufacturer's IFU. Pre-test dimensional inspection confirmed all screws within specification. Sample size was determined by a power analysis targeting 80% power to detect a 5% difference in stiffness (α=0.05, σ estimated from pilot data).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-test-samples",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Minimum N=8 specimens from a documented production lot; testing at ≥2 accredited laboratories; power analysis justifying sample size; pre-test dimensional inspection. Achieved: N=11 across two ISO 17025 labs; power analysis documented; all specimens within specification."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 loading condition (quasi-static compression-bending, 10° offset). The required Gradation 4 would demand testing across at least two loading configurations or loading rates to bracket the operating envelope. Resource and timeline constraints limited this validation campaign to a single condition. The shortfall is mitigated by: (1) the global sensitivity analysis confirming that loading-rate variation within the operating envelope (1–5 mm/min) produces <0.5% change in stiffness; (2) the E/uval metric incorporating experimental uncertainty that implicitly accounts for minor inter-laboratory procedural differences; and (3) the conservative acceptance bound (<10% QoI difference) providing margin against uncharacterised condition variability. An OffsetRationale is provided in the DecisionRecord.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — Gradation 4 required, Gradation 3 achieved",
        "description": "Gradation 4 requires testing under ≥2 loading configurations or rates spanning the operating envelope. Gradation 3 achieved: single ASTM F1717 quasi-static condition tested at two independent laboratories. Shortfall offset by sensitivity analysis and conservative acceptance bounds."
      },
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nc3-mrl5-accepted-2026/factor/test-conditions"
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "A formal equivalency mapping was performed between experimental inputs and FEA inputs. Screw geometry was transferred from CAD nominal dimensions corrected by CMM offsets. Sawbones block geometry was measured post-test (callipers, ±0.1 mm) and matched to FEA block dimensions. Applied displacement boundary conditions in FEA replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture kinematics (pin-pin, 10° offset) verified by fixture drawing review. Locking torque was converted to an equivalent pre-tension using a torque-tension relationship calibrated on a torque cell. Equivalency report EQR-2024-007 documents all mappings and residual discrepancies (<2% in all parameters).",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-equiv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "All primary model inputs must be traceable to measured experimental quantities with documented mapping and residual discrepancy <5%. Achieved: formal equivalency report; all discrepancies <2%."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "rationale": "Three QoIs are compared: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. For each QoI, the validation metric E/uval (ASME V&V 10.1) is computed incorporating both model-form uncertainty (from sensitivity analysis) and experimental measurement uncertainty (from inter-specimen variability and instrument calibration). All four validation results (stiffness Lab1, stiffness Lab2, yield force pooled, force at 40 mm pooled) return E/uval < 1.96, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance criterion. Graphical comparison of full force-displacement curves (0–50 mm) shows excellent agreement in both elastic and post-yield regimes. Gradation 5 achieved because three independent QoIs are compared with full uncertainty decomposition and graphical curve comparison.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-output",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria — Gradation 4 required, 5 achieved",
        "description": "E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; graphical comparison of full response curves; uncertainty decomposition documented. Achieved: E/uval ≤ 1.12 across all four comparisons; full F-D curve comparison; Sobol' decomposition of model uncertainty."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the direct regulatory endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and are the quantities used in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. A clinical relevance mapping (CRM-2024-002) traces each QoI to a clinically meaningful failure mode: stiffness to subsidence risk, yield force to acute fracture risk, and force at 40 mm to post-yield deformation tolerance. All three QoIs are directly observable in the validation experiment without transformation.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-qoi-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of QoIs acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "QoIs must be directly traceable to regulatory endpoints and clinically meaningful failure modes; clinical relevance mapping required. Achieved: three QoIs mapped to ASTM F1717 endpoints and clinical failure modes in CRM-2024-002."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the intended use scenario: the same screw geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), the same loading protocol (ASTM F1717 compression-bending), the same bone surrogate (40 pcf Sawbones), and the same construct configuration (two-level L4-L5 analogue) as the clinical use case. The validation is therefore a direct validation (not an analogy-based validation). The only deviation from clinical conditions is the use of a Sawbones surrogate rather than cadaveric bone, which is standard practice for ASTM F1717 and accepted by FDA guidance. This deviation is documented in relevance assessment RA-2024-007.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nc3-mrl5-val-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Relevance of validation activities acceptance criteria — Gradation 4",
        "description": "Validation activity must replicate intended use geometry, loading, and boundary conditions; deviations from clinical conditions must be documented and justified. Achieved: direct validation with documented Sawbones surrogate justification per FDA guidance."
      }
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nc3-mrl5-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/depuy-synthes-cba-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA ensemble for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw ASTM F1717 compression-bending prediction is accepted as credible for its intended regulatory use. All three primary QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) satisfy the pre-specified acceptance criterion E/uval < 1.96 across all four validation comparisons (maximum E/uval = 1.12). Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation level. The single shortfall — Test conditions (Gradation 3 achieved vs Gradation 4 required) — is offset by the global sensitivity analysis demonstrating that loading-rate variation within the operating envelope produces <0.5% change in primary QoIs, and by the conservative <10% QoI difference acceptance bound. The model risk level is assessed as 5 (highest) consistent with the Class II device classification and Medium decision consequence; the achieved credibility evidence is commensurate with this risk level. The provenance chain is complete from raw material characterisation data through mesh convergence, uncertainty quantification, and validation result generation. This package supports a 510(k) substantial equivalence submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw system.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z",
    "hasOffsetRationale": [
      {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/offset/nc3-mrl5-test-conditions",
        "type": "OffsetRationale",
        "name": "Offset rationale for Test conditions shortfall (Gradation 3 vs 4 required)",
        "refersToFactor": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nc3-mrl5-test-conditions",
        "justification": "The Test conditions factor achieved Gradation 3 (single ASTM F1717 quasi-static loading condition tested at two independent laboratories) against a required Gradation 4 (two or more loading configurations or rates). The shortfall is accepted because: (1) the global Sobol' sensitivity analysis (n=2048) demonstrates that crosshead displacement rate variation across the full operating envelope (1–5 mm/min) produces a maximum 0.4% change in construct stiffness and 0.6% change in force at 40 mm, well within the 10% acceptance bound; (2) the E/uval validation metric incorporates inter-laboratory procedural variability as part of the experimental uncertainty, providing implicit coverage of minor condition differences; (3) the conservative acceptance bound (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96) provides substantial margin above the observed maximum E/uval of 1.12; and (4) ASTM F1717 itself specifies a single quasi-static loading protocol as the regulatory standard, making multi-condition testing non-standard for this submission type. The residual risk from the Test conditions shortfall is therefore judged to be negligible relative to the demonstrated model accuracy and the breadth of the uncertainty characterisation."
      },
      {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nc3-mrl5-accepted-2026/offset/test-conditions",
